{"abstract":[{"text":"Dive into the details about what it means to support multitasking in iOS 13. Understand how previous best practices fit together with new ideas. Learn the nuances of structuring your application to support multiple windows, and how to instantiate your UI, handle windows coming and going, and manage your app’s underlying window resources.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-258-Architecting-Your-App-for-Multiple-Windows","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19"]]},"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"overridingTitle":"Watch Video (15 min)","type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc19\/258"}},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-258-architecting-your-app-for-multiple-windows"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"WWDC19","role":"sampleCode","title":"Architecting Your App for Multiple Windows","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}]},"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the new scene delegate based lifecycle:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"app delegate should still handle things like initializing\/cleaning up the whole process","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"it should not however handle things like setting up the UI or updating it when the app goes into foreground\/background - because this will now happen separately per session","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"additionally, application delegate is now notified when a scene is created or discarded","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"lifecycle delegate methods like ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiapplicationdelegate\/1623076-applicationwillenterforeground","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiapplicationdelegate\/1622956-applicationdidbecomeactive","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" etc. will not be called at all if scene lifecycle is enabled","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Modern lifecycle flow","level":2,"anchor":"Modern-lifecycle-flow","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Starting the app:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"AppDelegate","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiapplicationdelegate\/1622921-application"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AppDelegate"},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiapplicationdelegate\/3197905-application","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"->","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uisceneconfiguration","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" - return configuration for the scene","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"SceneDelegate","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiscenedelegate\/3197914-scene","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" - this is where you set up your new scene","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Scene 